author: Anthony Domanico
title: Lego 'Back to the Future' parody has tons of geeky cameos
text:
Roads? Where we're going, we don't need roads.
His "Back to the Future" short posted Sunday is just as impressive, with several characters and popular items from several geeky film and TV franchises making appearances.
Cars are whizzing through the air in the futuristic 2015 depicted in this animated short from Lego filmmaker MonsieurCaron , who impressed us with his Lego "Ghostbusters" short in 2014 .
Some of these are obvious, like Scooby-Doo and Shaggy in the Mystery Machine flying at the DeLorean, while others, like the Doctor's TARDIS and Nick Fury of Marvel cameos, require a watchful eye to spot.
There are at least 11 things to find in the clip, ranging from Luke Skywalker's lightsaber and Captain America's shield to Ant-Man, Rocket Raccoon and baby Groot.
'Back to the Future' gear for right now (pictures) 1 - 5 of 12 Next Prev The film was designed to celebrate "Back to the Future" day on October 21, the day Marty McFly and Doc Brown arrived in the future in "Back to the Future II."
You'll likely see much more "Back to the Future" content around the Internet over the next few days, so get your Mr. Fusion Home Energy Reactors loaded up for some time-traveling DeLorean goodness. Because, great Scott! The future is now!
Sort of .
